ngs_color\";s:7:\"#443f3f\";}}}}s:5:\"grids\";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"cells\";i:1;s:5:\"style\";a:5:{s:11:\"row_stretch\";s:4:\"full\";s:14:\"cell_alignment\";s:10:\"flex-start\";s:5:\"align\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"overlay\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"overlay_color\";s:7:\"#000000\";}}}s:10:\"grid_cells\";a:1:{i:0;a:4:{s:4:\"grid\";i:0;s:5:\"index\";i:0;s:6:\"weight\";i:1;s:5:\"style\";a:0:{}}}}'),(907,372,'panels_data','a:3:{s:7:\"widgets\";a:1:{i:0;a:7:{s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:10020:\"<div id=\"pg-3543-1\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-1-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-1-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<p>We are a few maverick freelancers who seized the opportunity to start a business and help out friends in the same situation. From this beginning we’ve harnessed the vigor of the small business owner and banded with them to increase value and produce better brands by expanding their online presence. Our clients all have one thing in common, they are creators of extraordinary things. They have another thing in common though and that is that they lack the time to do all the other important parts of business. We are your other half! The creators need to keep creating. They cannot be bogged down with learning and then actually implementing what we do.</p>\n<p>We do website operations and content marketing. This is THE BARE MINIMUM. We keep expenses low! We go in and once we have made sure you have found your sweet spot and identified your content tilt, we build you the platform.  When you have your cult following, then we setup your new enterprise.</p>\n<p>For your platform to work beyond a hobby based business, scalability is key. That means you need a team to get you to the next level. The few basic roles are: CCO Chief content officer (founder) this person is responsible for setting the overall editorial and content mission statement. Its many peoples responsibility to create content but it’s the CCOs responsibility that the ‘stories’ remain consistent and makes sense to the audience. In addition, the CCO must understand how the stories translate into results that address the organizations business issues, get new subscribers, keep subscribers, etc.. ; managing editor half storyteller half project manager, the ME executes the project plan on behalf of the CCO; whereas the cco focuses on strategy and some content, the managing editors job is all execution, working with the roles that well talk about in a little bit to make the content stories come alive, including scheduling the content. Chief listening officer, the role of the CLO is to function as air traffic control for social media and other content channels. This person is there to listen to the groups, maintain the conversation, and route and or notify feedback to other team members who can engage in appropriate conversations to you, to editorial, or perhaps to the sales team. This feedback mechanism is critical if the content is going to make a difference to your customers. The CLO must also monitor how the content is performing on all media sites, blogs and get that intelligence back to the ME. Director of audience, this person is charged with monitoring the members of your audience making sure all content creators are intamitely familiar with thei r characteristics their passion triggers and the direction you wan tthem to take. The DOA is also responsible for building assets like direct mail lists, direct email lists, and encryptions that can grow and be segmented as your content missions grows and expands. The channel master, wherever your content is headed social media, email, print, end user, the  CM is  responsible for getting the most and what works best on each channel. What works best on SlideShare? When should you send your reminder email newsletters and how frequently? Whats the proper ratio of owned versus curated content your business should distribute on twitter? Whos keeping track of mobile strategy and execution? Youchannel will look to this guy for answers. The Chief Technologist, as marketing information technology continues to merge there will be a need of at least one individual whos sole purpose is to leverage the proper use of these technologies into the content marketing process the person will be responsable for your publishing systems or the plumbing such as your website infrastructure and email systems and how they integrate together. The creative director, the desiugn and creative look to your content is more important thatn ever especially as creative and social channels become an increasingly important method of attracting and maintaining subscribers. The CD is responsible for the overall look and fell of all your content including your website your blog, images, photography, and every other piece of collateral you create. Influencer relations, the role formerly known as media relations will evolve into that a manager of influencers, this persons responsibilities include developing your hit list of influencers, maintaining your direct relationships with them, and integrating them into your marketing process in the most impactful ways. Freelancer and agency relations, as content demands continue to evolve and increase, your orgs relations with freelancers and other content venders will grow as well. The orgs need to cultivate their own expert teams and network and it is this persons job to negotiate rates and responsibilities are united in their work on behalf of your Content Inc. program. The Content curation director, as you begin to develop content assets you will have amazing opportunities to repackage and repurpose your content. But the role of the content manager is to look at all the assets being developed by the organization and strategize ways to create new pieces of content form them. This involves taking other people’s content, adding to it, enhancing it, and/or giving it a new context or perspective so that it evolves into a new piece of content. They are responsible for understanding the content assets available to work with including text image audio, effectively tagging, categorizing, and coordinating these materials into a data asset management system, working with the content marketing team on a clear channel plan, and developing and managing content marketing plan, developing and executing strategy by using existing resources.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2> </h2>\n<h2>Kevin Jones, The Founder</h2>\n<p>When I was young, I watched in awe as my father took an old MG sports car down to its frame, and then rebuilt the whole thing. I was hooked! I inherited his fascination for breaking things into their component parts. I love to figure out how things work, and then improve on the model to make it work better. And that’s exactly what I do at Ectobox.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, my professional background in Accounting keeps me grounded. I know that at the end of the day, the numbers have to add up. To grow your business you need more money coming in than going out. Your time, your people’s time, and your systems are all valuable resources your control. No matter how strong your company’s revenues are, if you’re bleeding money from these areas, it’s a drag on profits. I’m passionate about building, and my favorite thing to do is build businesses. Just like you, I work hard to make sure my own company is efficient in our processes and our systems, so I can keep my overhead low. And I personally oversee every project to make sure the job gets done right. Like you, I don’t like to waste money. I like to get things done. Just ask our <a title=\"Clients\" href=\"http://www.ectobox.com/clients/\">clients</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-2\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-2-0\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \"> </div>\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-2-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-2-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<h2>OUR PROCESS</h2>\n</div>\n<div id=\"panel-3543-2-1-1\" class=\"ppb-block ppb-no-mobile-spacing\">\n<p>We take the builder\'s approach of \"measure twice, cut once\". That\'s how carpenters avoid costly mistakes, and it makes the same good sense in the world of custom software design.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-4\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-4-0\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-4-0-0\" class=\"ppb-block\">\n<h2>OUR VALUES</h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"pg-3543-5\" class=\"panel-grid ppb-row\">\n<div class=\"ppb-row panel-row-style panel-row-style- ppb-stretch-full-width\">\n<div class=\"panel-grid-cell-container\">\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-5-0\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \"> </div>\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-5-1\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\"panel-3543-5-1-0\" class=\"ppb-block infobox_about\">\n<h2>WE ARE HONEST</h2>\n<div class=\"woo-sc-hr\"> </div>\n<ul>\n<li>We don’t sell what you don’t need.</li>\n<li>We won\'t lie to you.</li>\n<li>We guarantee a fit between the project and the team or we won\'t accept the work.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"panel-3543-5-1-1\" class=\"ppb-block infobox_about\">\n<h2>WE ARE DEPENDABLE</h2>\n<div class=\"woo-sc-hr\"> </div>\n<ul>\n<li>We\'ll be there.</li>\n<li>We won\'t flake out on you.</li>\n<li>We will be available.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"pgc-3543-5-2\" class=\"ppb-col panel-grid-cell \">\n<div id=\