aying we are both remarkable at what we do. But being remarkable has not been enough, has it?  So we must combine forces.  </p><p>Its quite simple you make content, I put it in front of the right peoples smiling faces, and we both reap the benefits, right?</p><p>See for your platform to work beyond a hobby based business, scalability is key. That means you need a team to get you to the next level....</p><p>... and my team has mastered The Three Phase Growth Plan.  It is the same plan that has worked for others that are EXACTLY in your situation.  It\'s not going to be easy, but knowing you are headed in the right direction will make all the difference and you might even make some friends along the way.</p><p>But before that plan even goes into motion something even more powerful graces it with its energies...</p><p>Get this!  When you send in your Expansion Idea it gets uploaded to a flash drive in Tibet where a monastery full of the most spiritual monks meditate to check basic viability of that idea in this market.  Chakras are performed.  Auras can flare. And if the idea marinades in Earth\'s ether just right and with enough energy to compel a white dove to soar from Tibet to New York whilst carrying that flash drive, then the idea was meant to be.  Suggested tweaks or additions will come in the form of intuition which we will communicate to you upon visiting for tea. Namaste.</p><p> </p><p>But enough about the initial process. What happens after that?</p><p> </p><p>Well, here is one way to think about the happenings:</p><p>Imagine your new Frankenstein Cyborg Baby <strong>creation</strong> is ready and it is just great.  You just know that they are gonna be the newest and coolest, and totally replace robot butlers forever.  But you are stuck selling them to a few people out of your garage which doesn\'t work well and brings you away from the fun part, like coming up with a better design for its fully reticulating neck and programming it to collect cobwebs off the ceiling.</p><p>That\'s where I come in.... so I build you a fancy store to sell them in making it all look very professional. Well call that <strong>development.</strong></p><p>We talk some more and while you like the store you would like it more if people were actually going into it....</p><p>So here is where it gets interesting.  I plan an event at The Festival which will demonstrate your Creation\'s cool abilities and I paint a sign saying ‘The Creation Demonstration coming to The Festival, Friday’, that’s <strong>advertising</strong>.</p><p>If you make an army of Scaled Down Abominable Creations and we walk them into town as they carry that sign, that’s <strong>promotion</strong>.</p><p>If the army gets hacked, starts taking over the world, and The Daily Show writes a story about it, that’s <strong>publicity</strong>.</p><p>And if I get the world to then laugh about it, that’s <strong>public relations</strong>.</p><p>If the town’s citizens go to see your creation, I show them the many ways it can entertain and make them happier, explain how much fun they’ll have spending money on one, answer their questions and ultimately, they buy a lot at the event, that’s <strong>sales</strong>.</p><p>And if I planned this entire thing, that’s <strong>marketing.</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>This is the secret to your success</strong> and what we do in a nutshell!!  The only difference is we do this all online, so it is called <strong>WEB development and marketing.</strong></p><p>So there is the secret!</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Also, the universe is telling me that by getting our <strong>monthly newsletter</strong> you will become fully enlightened and reach nirvana... as long as your nirvana is growing your business. Namaste.</p><p> </p>\";s:6:\"filter\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"panels_info\";a:7:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"WP_Widget_Black_Studio_TinyMCE\";s:3:\"raw\";b:0;s:4:\"grid\";i:3;s:4:\"cell\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";i:3;s:9:\"widget_id\";s:36:\"be8e3446-071d-4667-9368-945b8158bc49\";s:5:\"style\";a:5:{s:18:\"background_display\";s:4:\"tile\";s:10:\"font_color\";s:7:\"#ffffff\";s:17:\"content_alignment\";s:4:\"left\";s:11:\"title_color\";s:7:\"#ffffff\";s:14:\"headings_color\";s:7:\"#ffffff\";}}}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"visual\";s:5:\"title\";s:53:\"Most Recent Articles on Web Development and Marketing\";s:4:\"text\";s:158:\"<p>Front end development</p><p> </p><p>Content advertising</p><p>A custom plan to target your audience usingn what ever stream of information they trust.</p>\";s:6:\"filter\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"panels_info\";a:7:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"WP_Widget_Black_Studio_TinyMCE\";s:3:\"raw\";b:0;s:4:\"grid\";i:4;s:4:\"cell\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";i:4;s:9:\"widget_id\";s:36:\"d126a64f-3679-4199-8440-44206b01ea05\";s:5:\"style\";a:4:{s:18:\"background_display\";s:4:\"tile\";s:17:\"content_alignment\";s:4:\"left\";s:11:\"title_color\";s:7:\"#777777\";s:14:\"headings_color\";s:7:\"#777777\";}}}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"visual\";s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"\"We Believe the Best Business Model Should Win\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:3946:\"<h3>If you are ready to take on more clientele, then it is time for you to get an affordable professionally created and managed online presence. Naturally, we are the team to do that!</h3><h3>Why us?  What makes us so special?  Well, we are a team of maverick FREE-LANCERS (yup, mind blown) who are familiar with working together.  We are able to tailor every man hour.  Since it is such a modular work environment this means you are never paying money for something you do not need.  Yes, waste has got to be my number one pet peeve.</h3><h3>Let me illustrate this idea.  Lets say you need a fully loaded, connected, custom website in a few weeks. Even after you vet them, A free lancer or two would burn out trying to do that.  I wonder how the product would look...  I wonder how clean it would be under the hood...  I wonder what would happen to your asset if one or both of those freelancers moved... would you still get post project support for your asset?  Anyway, among freelancers we are the most affordable, because as a group of freelancers our networks are stable when you multiply connections.  We aren\'t spending time finding work, so we don\'t need to charge exorbitant prices (150/hr minimum). And going to a corporation as a viable alternative to freelancers for a project like this is laughable. You would be paying for the entire scrum management team and their pensions. Talk about overhead. Not to mention they might treat you like a number.  They might wonder why you are coming to them with such a dinky project.</h3><h3>You get the benefits of hiring a large businesses as well as all of the benefits of hiring a freelancer,  with none of the negatives.   We have a name to uphold its called accountability</h3><h3>So this is what really sets us apart.  Why isn\'t anyone else doing this? Putting together a team of free lancers.  Well, collaboration has never been so easy.  Flower City Online has created a seamless workflow, making it possible for us if we wanted to have 14 people on a job each putting in an hour a day and sending it to the master.</h3><h3>Again, we promise we won\'t quote you a price unless it is a win-win for both of us.  Our goal is to earn your business for the long term.  I hope you have recognized my transparency throughout, because this is how I have always done business.  So please, send us your thoughts today!  I hope we can work together to grow your business.</h3><h3> </h3><p> </p><p> </p><p>THE FREEDOM TO FREELANCE IS AT AN ALL TIME HIGH</p><h3>You don\'t see many of these teams because corporations are safe and cushy and offer many benefits and would steal freelancers away too quickly... but this is changing.  Even some of our developers are working full time and contribute when they can, but that is a busy life style with a family.  No, but most of our developers have been working for us since they first became what the corporate world would call junior developers.  Because of this experience they know so much more than software development.  Going to the 9-5 and just coding would get boring.  We sacrifice full time benefits though.  Our loss your gain.  This is happening for the same reason Crowd Companies are a thing.</h3><h3>Also you dont see em bc of the markets. Demand for small jobs from small businesses born out of the satisfying the tiniest , but still possibly deepest of niches is growing, and thus modular labor is growing. This is because of work environements being more fluid. THis is becasue of all the niches getting grooved out becasue of the internet content cornucopia. As the world transitions to the online world we will only see more of this. The other day I say an 80 year old learning wordpress. This will be common place. This is the easily observable and trend and it makes sense. Knowing how to use a computer wasn\'t a thing 15 years ago. It still is not a necessary thing. But soon it will be.</h3><p> </p>\";s:6:\"filter\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"panels_info\";a:6:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"WP_Widget_Black_Studio_TinyMCE\";s:4:\"grid\";i:5;s:4:\"cell\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";i:5;s:9:\"widget_id\";s:36:\"a6db3609-eddb-45ef-9bc1-ced03e60478c\";s:5:\"style\";a:6:{s:27:\"background_image_attachment\";b:0;s:18:\"background_display\";s:4:\"tile\";s:10:\"font_color\";s:7:\"#ffffff\";s:17:\"content_alignment\";s:4:\"left\";s:11:\"title_color\";s:7:\"#ffffff\";s:14:\"headings_color\";s:7:\"#ffffff\";}}}i:6;a:3:{s:11:\"panels_data\";a:3:{s:7:\"widgets\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"type\";s:6:\"visual\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:16:\"<p>Main Menu</p>\";s:6:\"filter\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"panels_info\";a:6:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"WP_Widget_Black_Studio_TinyMCE\";s:4:\"grid\";i:0;s:4:\"cell\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";i:0;s:9:\"widget_id\";s:36:\"14a5e4d9-b14c-404f-bbe3-4bd01ed3f5fe\";s:5:\"style\";a:15:{s:2:\"id\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"widget_css\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"mobile_css\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"padding\";s:0:\"\";s:14:\"mobile_padding\";s:0:\"\"